  "intro": "The beam is yours. The seed-stones only cross the void under its pull — one hurls, one lands them true.",
  "designNotes": "Tractor relay over a central chasm. Three plate-islands rise from the void, unreachable on foot (>4.5 m gaps) — a stone can only arrive by tractor beam. plateA and plateB need mass 1; plateC needs mass 2. There are only THREE free seed-stones (seedA/B/C) but the plates demand 1+1+2 = 4 mass, so the pair is one stone short. Pressing plateA AND plateB opens the cage (openWhen) holding the fourth stone, seedD. Order is forced: land A and B first, retrieve seedD, then feed seedC+seedD onto plateC. plateC sits behind the central spar, so the operator must rotate aimRing to state 1 to swing the deflector chute and clear the throw-line to island C (mechanism). Two drifters patrol the ring ledges and can be tractored off into the void. Final gate spans mass (plates) + mechanism (aimRing) + combat.",
  "fog": { "color": "#5c4a68", "density": 0.018 },
